.START 

Consumer prices in the 12-nation European Community rose a moderate 0.2% in August and 0.3% in July, according to EC figures. 

The August figure is provisional. 

Inflation during the two months was highest in Portugal, where prices rose 1% in July and 1.8% in August, and in Spain, where prices increased 1.6% in July and 0.2% in August. 

The EC statistics agency, Eurostat, said that EC inflation for the 12 months to August was 5.1%.
That is slightly higher than the U.S., at 4.7%, and well above Japan, at 2.4%. 

